cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about shallow discourse parsing, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the use of machine learning suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Finally, the use of the UIMA framework and ClearTK suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
